Project Idea:
    We developed a mobile-first web application that helps users discover food and drink pairings.

    Users can browse a curated selection of foods and drinks and see suggested pairings immediately without logging in. Logged-in users can additionally search manually by typing any food or drink name and apply personal preferences to receive filtered results tailored to them.

    The application supports two pairing directions:
        Food → Drink: user selects or types a food, receives drink recommendations
        Drink → Food: user selects or types a drink, receives food recommendations

    Logged-in users can customise three preference categories:
        Dietary restrictions (e.g., vegan, pescatarian, celiac / gluten-free)
        Alcohol mood notes (e.g., Light & Bubbling, Rich & Warming, Earthy & Traditional)
        Flavour profiles (e.g., dry, earthy, crisp / refreshing)

    These preferences are applied as filters to personalise pairing results. The system uses rule-based filtering logic against a structured Firestore database rather than AI.

    The application also includes a Contact Us page allowing users to send messages directly to the team.

Technologies used:
    Frontend: React with TypeScript, React Router
    Backend: Node.js with Express
    Database: Google Firestore (NoSQL)
    Authentication: Firebase Authentication (email/password and Google sign-in)
    Project Management: Jira, GitLab